quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  8,34,"Yet why should Allah not punish them when they bar others from the Inviolable Mosque, though they are not its guardians? Rather its guardians are none except the mindful<i class=""s"">(of God) </i>, but most of them do not know."
  8,35,"And their prayer at the House was nothing but whistling and clapping—so taste<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>the punishment for what you{1}used to deny.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 3rd person to 2nd person.
  8,36,"Indeed, those who have denied spend their wealths to bar<i class=""s"">(others) </i>from the way of Allah. So they will spend it, then it will become a source of sorrow for them and then they will be overcome. And those who have denied are herded to Hell."
  8,37,"That Allah may distinguish the nasty from the good, and heap the nasty<i class=""s"">(things) </i>on top of one another and pile them together and set it up in Hell; those are the losers."
  8,38,"Tell<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>those who have denied that if they desist, they will be forgiven whatever has already passed. But if they return—then the rule of<i class=""s"">(God regarding) </i>the ancients is already established."
  8,39,"And combat<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>them until there is no more religious persecution and religion is all for Allah. But if they desist—then Allah is All-Seeing of what <span class=""h"">they<sup foot_note=""80135"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">do</span>."
  8,40,"And if they turn away, then know<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>that Allah is your Patron; what an excellent Patron and what an excellent Supporter!"
